  "commentary": "With SPX at 6602.32 sitting just below the 6605 max positive gamma wall (+22.7B), dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that level, creating natural resistance. The PIN regime with 50.1B total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting flows, and the proximity to the GEX flip at 6612 means we're in maximum stabilization territory where dealers will fade directional moves. Key levels: heavy selling pressure at 6605-6610, while any break below 6590 flips dealers into buy-mode amplification.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590-6610 with choppy, range-bound action.",
